145#define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
146 while (false) { \
147 *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
148 }
149
181template <class T>
182class Local {
183 public:
184 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
185 template <class S>
186 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
187 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
193 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
194 }
195
199 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
200
204 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
205
206 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
207
208 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
209
216 template <class S>
217 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
218 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
219 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
220 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
221 if (b == nullptr) return false;
222 return *a == *b;
223 }
224
225 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
226 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
227 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
228 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
229 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
230 if (b == nullptr) return false;
231 return *a == *b;
232 }
233
240 template <class S>
241 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
242 return !operator==(that);
243 }
244
245 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
246 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
247 return !operator==(that);
248 }
249
255 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
256#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
257 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
258 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
259 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
260#endif
261 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
262 }
263
269 template <class S>
270 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
271 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
272 }
273
279 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
280 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
281 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
282 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, const TracedGlobal<T>& that);
283
284 private:
285 friend class Utils;
286 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
287 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
288 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
289 template<class F> friend class Local;
290 template <class F>
291 friend class MaybeLocal;
292 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
293 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
294 friend class String;
295 friend class Object;
296 friend class Context;
297 friend class Isolate;
298 friend class Private;
299 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
300 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
301 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
302 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
303 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
304 friend class HandleScope;
305 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
306 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
307 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
308 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
309 template <class F>
310 friend class ReturnValue;
311 template <class F>
312 friend class TracedGlobal;
313
314 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
315 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
316 T* val_;
317};

342 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)

345 }

347 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
348
353 template <class S>
354 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
355 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
356 return !IsEmpty();
357 }
358
363 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
364
369 template <class S>
370 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
371 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
372 }
373
374 private:
375 T* val_;
376};

399static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
400static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
401
402template <typename T>
403class WeakCallbackInfo {
404 public:
405 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
406
407 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
408 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
409 Callback* callback)
410 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
411 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
412 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
413 }
414 }
415
416 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
417 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
418 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
419
420 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
421 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
422 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
423 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
424 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
425 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
426 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
427
428 private:
429 Isolate* isolate_;
430 T* parameter_;
431 Callback* callback_;
432 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
433};
434
435
436// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
437// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
438// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
439// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
440// possible to request a second pass callback.
441enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
442

487 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
488 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;

531 V8_INLINE void SetWeak();

563

574 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
575 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
576 friend class Object;
577
578 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
579 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);

582};

632template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
633 public:
637 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
643 template <class S>
644 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
645 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
646 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
647 }
653 template <class S, class M2>
654 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
655 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
656 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
657 }
664 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
665 Copy(that);
666 }
667 template <class S, class M2>
668 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
669 Copy(that);
670 }
671 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
672 Copy(that);
673 return *this;
674 }
675 template <class S, class M2>
676 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
677 Copy(that);
678 return *this;
679 }
685 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
686 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
687 }
688
689 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
690 template <class S>
691 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
692#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
693 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
694 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
695 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
696#endif
697 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
698 }
699
700 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
701 template <class S>
702 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
703 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
704 }
705
706 private:
707 friend class Isolate;
708 friend class Utils;
709 template<class F> friend class Local;
710 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
711 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
712
713 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
714 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
715 template<class S, class M2>
716 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
717};

1118class ScriptOriginOptions {
1119 public:
1120 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1121 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1122 bool is_module = false)
1123 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1124 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1125 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1126 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1127 : flags_(flags &
1128 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1129
1130 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1131 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1132 }
1133 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1134 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1135 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1136
1137 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1138
1139 private:
1140 enum {
1141 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1142 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1143 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1144 kIsModule = 1 << 3
1145 };
1146 const int flags_;
1147};

1361class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1362 public:
1370 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1371 enum BufferPolicy {
1372 BufferNotOwned,
1373 BufferOwned
1374 };
1375
1376 CachedData()
1377 : data(nullptr),
1378 length(0),
1379 rejected(false),
1380 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1381
1382 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1383 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1384 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1385 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1386 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1387 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1388 ~CachedData();
1389 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1390 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1391 const uint8_t* data;
1392 int length;
1393 bool rejected;
1394 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1395
1396 // Prevent copying.
1397 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1398 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1399 };
1400
1404 class Source {
1405 public:
1406 // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1407 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1408 CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1409 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1410 CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1411 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1412
1413 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1414 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1415 // alive.
1416 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1417
1418 V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1419
1420 // Prevent copying.
1421 Source(const Source&) = delete;
1422 Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1423
1424 private:
1425 friend class ScriptCompiler;
1426
1427 Local<String> source_string;
1428
1429 // Origin information
1430 Local<Value> resource_name;
1431 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1432 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1433 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1434 Local<Value> source_map_url;
1435 Local<PrimitiveArray> host_defined_options;
1436
1437 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1438 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1439 // set when calling a compile method.
1440 CachedData* cached_data;
1441 };

1914 GC,
1915 PARSER,
1916 BYTECODE_COMPILER,
1917 COMPILER,
1918 OTHER,
1919 EXTERNAL,
1920 IDLE
1921};

1923// A RegisterState represents the current state of registers used
1924// by the sampling profiler API.
1925struct RegisterState {
1926 RegisterState() : pc(nullptr), sp(nullptr), fp(nullptr), lr(nullptr) {}
1927 void* pc; // Instruction pointer.
1928 void* sp; // Stack pointer.
1929 void* fp; // Frame pointer.
1930 void* lr; // Link register (or nullptr on platforms without a link register).
1931};
1932
1933// The output structure filled up by GetStackSample API function.
1934struct SampleInfo {
1935 size_t frames_count; // Number of frames collected.
1936 StateTag vm_state; // Current VM state.
1937 void* external_callback_entry; // External callback address if VM is
1938 // executing an external callback.
1939};

3824template<typename T>
3825class ReturnValue {
3826 public:
3827 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3828 : value_(that.value_) {
3829 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3830 }
3831 // Local setters
3832 template <typename S>
3833 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3834 template <typename S>
3835 V8_INLINE void Set(const TracedGlobal<S>& handle);
3836 template <typename S>
3837 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3838 // Fast primitive setters
3839 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3840 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3841 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3842 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3843 // Fast JS primitive setters
3844 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3845 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3846 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3847 // Convenience getter for Isolate

3853
3854 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3855 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3856 // value.
3857 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3858
3859 private:
3860 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3861 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3862 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3863 template <class F, class G, class H>
3864 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3865 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
3866 V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();

3868 internal::Address* value_;
3869};

6363 return source_;
6364 }

6366 const char** dependencies() const { return deps_; }
6367 void set_auto_enable(bool value) { auto_enable_ = value; }
6368 bool auto_enable() { return auto_enable_; }
6369

6372 void operator=(const Extension&) = delete;

6376 size_t source_length_; // expected to initialize before source_

6457 size_t max_old_space_size_;

6949struct JitCodeEvent {
6950 enum EventType {
6951 CODE_ADDED,
6952 CODE_MOVED,
6953 CODE_REMOVED,
6954 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6955 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6956 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6957 };
6958 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6959 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6960 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6961 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6962 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6963 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6964
6965 // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
6966 // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
6967 // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
6968 // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
6969 // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
6970 // function.
6971 enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
6972
6973 // Type of event.
6974 EventType type;
6975 CodeType code_type;
6976 // Start of the instructions.
6977 void* code_start;
6978 // Size of the instructions.
6979 size_t code_len;
6980 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6981 Local<UnboundScript> script;
6982 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6983 // code line information which is returned from the
6984 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6985 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6986 void* user_data;
6987
6988 struct name_t {
6989 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6990 // zero-terminated.
6991 const char* str;
6992 // Number of chars in str.
6993 size_t len;
6994 };
6995
6996 struct line_info_t {
6997 // PC offset
6998 size_t offset;
6999 // Code position
7000 size_t pos;
7001 // The position type.
7002 PositionType position_type;
7003 };
7004
7005 union {
7006 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
7007 struct name_t name;
7008
7009 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
7010 struct line_info_t line_info;
7011
7012 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
7013 void* new_code_start;
7014 };
7015
7016 Isolate* isolate;
7017};
7018
7024enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7025 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7026 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7027 // Throughput may be throttled.
7028 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7029 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7030 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7031 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7032 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7033 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7034 // in this mode.
7035 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7036 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7037 // turn off latency optimizations.
7038 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7039};
7040
7044enum JitCodeEventOptions {
7045 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
7046 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
7047 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
7048};

7246 protected:

8909template <class T>
8910class Maybe {
8911 public:
8912 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8913 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8914
8918 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8919
8924 V8_INLINE void Check() const {
8925 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8926 }
8927
8932 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8933 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8934 return IsJust();
8935 }
8936
8941 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8942 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8943 return value_;
8944 }
8945
8950 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8951 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8952 }
8953
8954 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8955 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8956 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8957 }
8958
8959 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8960 return !operator==(other);
8961 }
8962
8963 private:
8964 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8965 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8966
8967 bool has_value_;
8968 T value_;
8969
8970 template <class U>
8971 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8972 template <class U>
8973 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8974};
8975
8976template <class T>
8977inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
8978 return Maybe<T>();
8979}
8980
8981template <class T>
8982inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
8983 return Maybe<T>(t);
8984}
8985
8986// A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
8987template <>
8988class Maybe<void> {
8989 public:
8990 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
8991 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
8992
8993 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8994 return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
8995 }
8996
8997 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8998 return !operator==(other);
8999 }
9000
9001 private:
9002 struct JustTag {};
9003
9004 Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
9005 explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
9006
9007 bool is_valid_;
9008
9009 template <class U>
9010 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9011 friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
9012};
9013
9014inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

9439 return js_stack_comparable_address_;
9440 }
9441

9443 friend class internal::Isolate;
9444
9445 Local<Context> backup_incumbent_context_;
9446 uintptr_t js_stack_comparable_address_ = 0;
9447 const BackupIncumbentScope* prev_ = nullptr;
9448 };

9459};

9814 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
9815 if (this != &rhs) {
9816 this->Reset();
9817 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
9818 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
9819 V8::MoveGlobalReference(
9820 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
9821 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
9822 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
9823 }
9824 }
9825 return *this;
9826}

9947template<typename T>
9948void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
9949 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9950 typedef internal::Internals I;
9951 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
9952 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
9953 return;
9954 }
9955 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9956}
9957
9958template<typename T>
9959void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
9960 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9961 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
9962 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
9963 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
9964 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
9965 return;
9966 }
9967 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
9968}
9969
9970template<typename T>
9971void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
9972 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
9973 typedef internal::Internals I;
9974 int root_index;
9975 if (value) {
9976 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
9977 } else {
9978 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
9979 }
9980 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
9981}

9985 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
9986 typedef internal::Internals I;
9987 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
9988}

9994 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
9995}

10200
10201Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
10202#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10203 typedef internal::Address A;
10204 typedef internal::Internals I;
10205 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
10206 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
10207 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
10208 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
10209 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
10210 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
10211 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
10212 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
10213 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
10214#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
10215 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
10216 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
10217 value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<int32_t>(value));
10218#endif
10219 internal::Isolate* isolate =
10220 internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
10221 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
10222 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10223 }
10224#endif
10225 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
10226}
10227
10228
10229void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
10230#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10231 typedef internal::Address A;
10232 typedef internal::Internals I;
10233 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
10234 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
10235 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
10236 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
10237 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
10238 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
10239 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
10240 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
10241 return I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, offset);
10242 }
10243#endif
10244 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
10245}

10253
10254
10255Local<String> String::Empty(Isolate* isolate) {
10256 typedef internal::Address S;
10257 typedef internal::Internals I;
10258 I::CheckInitialized(isolate);
10259 S* slot = I::GetRoot(isolate, I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
10260 return Local<String>(reinterpret_cast<String*>(slot));
10261}

10263
10264String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
10265 typedef internal::Address A;
10266 typedef internal::Internals I;
10267 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10268
10269 ExternalStringResource* result;
10270 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
10271 void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
10272 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
10273 } else {
10274 result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
10275 }
10276#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10277 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
10278#endif
10279 return result;
10280}

10283String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
10284 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
10285 typedef internal::Address A;
10286 typedef internal::Internals I;
10287 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10288 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
10289 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
10290 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
10291 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
10292 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
10293 void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
10294 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
10295 } else {
10296 resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
10297 }
10298#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10299 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
10300#endif
10301 return resource;

10806
10807int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10808 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10809 typedef internal::Internals I;
10810 constexpr int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
10811 int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10812 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10813 int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10814 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10815 int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
10816 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
10817 I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
10818
10819 // Embedders are weird: we see both over- and underflows here. Perform the
10820 // addition with unsigned types to avoid undefined behavior.
10821 const int64_t amount =
10822 static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes) +
10823 static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory));
10824 *external_memory = amount;
10825
10826 int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
10827 static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory) -
10828 static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_at_last_mc));
10829 // Only check memory pressure and potentially trigger GC if the amount of
10830 // external memory increased.
10831 if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
10832 CheckMemoryPressure();
10833 }
10834
10835 if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
10836 const int64_t lower_limit = *external_memory_limit + change_in_bytes;
10837 if (lower_limit > I::kExternalAllocationSoftLimit)
10838 *external_memory_limit = lower_limit;
10839 } else if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
10840 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10841 }
10842 return *external_memory;
10843}
10844
10845Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
10846#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10847 typedef internal::Address A;
10848 typedef internal::Internals I;
10849 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10850 A embedder_data =
10851 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
10852 int value_offset =
10853 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
10854 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
10855#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
10856 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
10857 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
10858 value =
10859 I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<int32_t>(value));
10860#endif
10861 internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
10862 *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
10863 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
10864 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10865#else
10866 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
10867#endif
10868}
10869
10870
10871void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
10872#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10873 typedef internal::Address A;
10874 typedef internal::Internals I;
10875 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10876 A embedder_data =
10877 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
10878 int value_offset =
10879 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
10880 return I::ReadRawField<void*>(embedder_data, value_offset);
10881#else
10882 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
10883#endif
10884}
